task_6.query_used: Search GitHub or professional coding platforms for technical contributions in AI or Quality Engineering
task_6.data:
I found limited information on Muhammad Aqib Iqbal's technical contributions in AI or Quality Engineering on GitHub or professional coding platforms. However, he has been involved in several academic publications related to these fields.

One notable publication is "Towards Sustainable AI: A Comprehensive Framework for Green AI," co-authored by Abdulaziz Tabbakh, Lisan Al Amin, Mahbubul Islam, GM Iqbal Mahmud, Imranul Kabir Chowdhury, and Md Saddam Hossain Mukta. This paper, published on November 15, 2024, discusses the environmental impact of AI and proposes a framework for sustainable AI practices. ([gmiqbal.github.io](https://gmiqbal.github.io/_pages/publications-data/?utm_source=openai))

Another significant work is "Application of Artificial Intelligence in Reverse Logistics: A Bibliometric and Network Analysis," co-authored by Oyshik Bhowmik, Sudipta Chowdhury, Jahid Hasan Ashik, GM Iqbal Mahmud, Md Muzahid Khan, and Niamat Ullah Ibne Hossain. Published in September 2024, this study analyzes the use of AI in reverse logistics, identifying key contributors and emerging trends. ([gmiqbal.github.io](https://gmiqbal.github.io/_pages/publications-data/?utm_source=openai))

Additionally, Muhammad Aqib Iqbal has a profile on Codester, a platform for developers to buy and sell code and app templates. His profile, under the username "Aqibofficial," lists an Android app template called "Red Pro VPN." The profile indicates he is based in Lahore, Pakistan, and has been a member since July 2021. ([codester.com](https://www.codester.com/Aqibofficial?utm_source=openai))

While there is limited information on his GitHub contributions, these publications and his presence on Codester suggest active involvement in AI and Quality Engineering projects.
